---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = "Building Service Terms - Arron Bennett Building Contractors";
const pageDescription = "Building Service Terms & Conditions for Arron Bennett Building Contractors. Payment terms, warranties, project timelines, and service agreements for construction work.";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": pageTitle,
  "description": pageDescription
};
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} schema={schema}>
  <div class="min-h-screen">
    <section class="hero bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-600 to-blue-800 text-white py-16 lg:py-20 px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6">
          Building Service Terms & Conditions
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-blue-100">
          Terms for Engaging Our Building Services
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms and Conditions ("Terms") govern the provision of building and construction services by Arron Bennett Building Contractors ("we", "us", "our"). By engaging our services, you ("the Client") agree to be bound by these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Definitions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>"Company", "we", "us", "our":</strong> Refers to Arron Bennett Building Contractors</li>
          <li><strong>"Client", "you", "your":</strong> Refers to the person or entity engaging our services</li>
          <li><strong>"Services":</strong> Building, construction, renovation, and related services we provide</li>
          <li><strong>"Project":</strong> The specific work to be undertaken as agreed in writing</li>
          <li><strong>"Quote":</strong> The estimated cost of services provided to you</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Services</h2>
        <h3>3.1 Scope of Services</h3>
        <p>We provide building and construction services including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Extensions and renovations</li>
          <li>New builds</li>
          <li>Roofing and structural work</li>
          <li>General building maintenance</li>
          <li>Project management</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Quotations</h3>
        <p>
          All quotations are valid for 30 days from the date of issue unless otherwise stated.
          Quotations are based on the information provided by the client at the time of request.
          Any changes to the project scope may result in revised pricing.
        </p>

        <h3>3.3 Acceptance of Quote</h3>
        <p>
          A contract is formed when you accept our written quotation. Acceptance can be confirmed by:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Signing and returning the quotation</li>
          <li>Written confirmation via email</li>
          <li>Payment of the initial deposit</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Payment Terms</h2>
        <h3>4.1 Deposits</h3>
        <p>
          A deposit may be required before work commences. The deposit amount will be specified in your quotation
          and is typically between 10-30% of the total project cost.
        </p>

        <h3>4.2 Stage Payments</h3>
        <p>
          For larger projects, payments may be staged according to project milestones as outlined in your contract.
          All stage payments must be made before the next phase of work begins.
        </p>

        <h3>4.3 Final Payment</h3>
        <p>
          Final payment is due upon completion of the project and your satisfaction with the work.
          Retention may be held as specified in the contract for a specified period.
        </p>

        <h3>4.4 Late Payment</h3>
        <p>
          Late payments may incur interest charges as permitted by the Late Payment of Commercial Debts
          (Interest) Act 1998. We reserve the right to suspend work if payments are not received as agreed.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Client Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>The client agrees to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate information about the project requirements</li>
          <li>Obtain and provide necessary permissions and permits</li>
          <li>Ensure access to the site during working hours</li>
          <li>Remove or protect valuable items before work commences</li>
          <li>Provide utilities (water, electricity) as required</li>
          <li>Make prompt decisions on materials and specifications</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Our Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>We commit to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete work to a professional standard</li>
          <li>Comply with all relevant building regulations</li>
          <li>Maintain appropriate insurance coverage</li>
          <li>Work within agreed timescales where reasonably possible</li>
          <li>Leave the site clean and tidy at the end of each working day</li>
          <li>Minimize disruption to your property</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Project Timelines</h2>
        <h3>7.1 Start and Completion Dates</h3>
        <p>
          While we aim to meet all agreed timescales, completion dates are estimates and may be affected by:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Weather conditions</li>
          <li>Material availability</li>
          <li>Discovery of unforeseen structural issues</li>
          <li>Changes to project scope</li>
          <li>Delays in obtaining client decisions or approvals</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Delays</h3>
        <p>
          We will notify you promptly of any anticipated delays. We are not liable for delays beyond our reasonable control.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Variations and Changes</h2>
        <p>
          Any changes to the agreed project scope must be confirmed in writing. Variations may affect the project
          cost and timeline. We will provide a written quote for any additional work before proceeding.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Materials and Workmanship</h2>
        <h3>9.1 Materials</h3>
        <p>
          Unless otherwise agreed, we will select appropriate materials for your project. You have the right to
          approve materials before installation. Alternative material choices may affect the project cost.
        </p>

        <h3>9.2 Existing Structures</h3>
        <p>
          We are not liable for the condition of existing structures unless specifically agreed in writing.
          Hidden defects discovered during work may require additional work and cost.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Guarantees and Warranties</h2>
        <h3>10.1 Workmanship Guarantee</h3>
        <p>
          We guarantee our workmanship for a period specified in your contract (typically 12 months from completion).
          This guarantee covers defects resulting from poor workmanship but does not cover:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Normal wear and tear</li>
          <li>Damage caused by the client or third parties</li>
          <li>Failure to maintain the work properly</li>
          <li>Defects in materials supplied by the client</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>10.2 Manufacturer Warranties</h3>
        <p>
          Materials and products are covered by manufacturer warranties where applicable. We will provide
          warranty documentation upon completion.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Insurance and Liability</h2>
        <h3>11.1 Public Liability Insurance</h3>
        <p>
          We maintain appropriate public liability insurance. We are liable for damage to your property
          caused by our negligence during the course of our work.
        </p>

        <h3>11.2 Limitation of Liability</h3>
        <p>
          Our total liability under these Terms shall not exceed the total contract value. We are not liable for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Indirect or consequential losses</li>
          <li>Loss of profits or business</li>
          <li>Damage caused by third parties</li>
          <li>Pre-existing defects not identified at the survey stage</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>12. Health and Safety</h2>
        <p>
          We maintain high health and safety standards on all projects. We comply with relevant legislation
          including the Construction (Design and Management) Regulations 2015.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Cancellation and Termination</h2>
        <h3>13.1 Client Cancellation</h3>
        <p>
          You may cancel the contract before work commences with written notice. If materials have been
          ordered, you may be charged for these costs plus an administration fee.
        </p>

        <h3>13.2 Our Right to Terminate</h3>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to terminate the contract if:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Payments are not made as agreed</li>
          <li>Site access is denied</li>
          <li>The client breaches these Terms</li>
          <li>Circumstances make it impossible to continue work safely</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>14. Complaints and Disputes</h2>
        <h3>14.1 Complaint Procedure</h3>
        <p>
          If you have any concerns about our work, please contact us immediately. We aim to resolve all
          complaints amicably and promptly.
        </p>

        <h3>14.2 Dispute Resolution</h3>
        <p>
          In the event of a dispute, we encourage resolution through negotiation or mediation before
          pursuing legal action.
        </p>

        <h2>15. Data Protection</h2>
        <p>
          We process your personal data in accordance with UK data protection legislation. Please refer to
          our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for full details on how we handle your information.
        </p>

        <h2>16. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          Any designs, plans, or documentation we create remain our intellectual property unless otherwise
          agreed in writing. You have a license to use these for the specific project only.
        </p>

        <h2>17. Subcontractors</h2>
        <p>
          We may use qualified subcontractors for specialist work. We remain responsible for all work
          carried out by subcontractors on your project.
        </p>

        <h2>18. Force Majeure</h2>
        <p>
          We are not liable for failure to perform our obligations due to events beyond our reasonable control,
          including but not limited to natural disasters, strikes, or government restrictions.
        </p>

        <h2>19. Entire Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms, together with any written quotation and contract, constitute the entire agreement
          between us. Any verbal representations made are not binding unless confirmed in writing.
        </p>

        <h2>20. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes will be subject to the
          exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
        </p>

        <h2>21. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated
          revision date. New projects will be subject to the terms in effect at the time of contract signing.
        </p>

        <h2>22. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Building Service Terms, please contact us:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:enquiries@arronbennettbuilding.co.uk">enquiries@arronbennettbuilding.co.uk</a></li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> 07773 463383</li>
          <li><strong>Address:</strong> Cornwall, United Kingdom</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6 my-8">
          <p class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Important Notice</p>
          <p class="text-blue-800">
            These terms and conditions apply to the provision of building and construction services only.
            For our website terms of use, please see our <a href="/terms-of-use" class="font-semibold underline">Website Terms of Use</a>.
            Specific project details will be outlined in individual contracts and quotations.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900">Ready to Start Your Project?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">
          If you have questions about our service terms or would like to discuss your building project, please get in touch.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/contact-us"
          class="inline-block bg-navy-900 text-white font-semibold px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-navy-800 transition-colors duration-200"
        >
          Contact Us Today
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: #374151;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    color: #1f2937;
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    color: #374151;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: #2563eb;
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .prose a:hover {
    color: #1d4ed8;
  }

  .hero {
    background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #2563eb 0%, #1e40af 100%);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .prose h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .prose h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
